## Issue Details
- **ID:** PAN-645
- **Title:** Tests: root Vitest config does not discover ActionsSection.test.tsx
- **URL:** https://github.com/eltmon/panopticon-cli/issues/645

## Description
The colocated frontend test `src/dashboard/frontend/src/components/inspector/ActionsSection.test.tsx` is not discovered by the root `npx vitest --run ...` invocation because the current include pattern only picks up `tests/**/*.test.ts` and `src/**/__tests__/**/*.test.ts`.

Impact:
- targeted root test runs report "No test files found" for this file
- inspector action coverage exists on disk but is easy to miss in normal verification

Expected:
- root Vitest should discover colocated `*.test.tsx` files under `src/dashboard/frontend/src/components/**`
- or the file should be moved under `__tests__` if that is the enforced convention

Acceptance criteria:
- running the root Vitest command against this file executes the test instead of returning "No test files found"
- the project has one clear convention for colocated vs `__tests__` frontend tests

